The statement `x + 0 = x` follows immediately from the definition of addition in any additive group, regardless of the other properties. Therefore, no proof that uses any of the given properties is necessary here.

But since the problem insists on using one of them, perhaps the most relevant is property 4 (`0 ∈ X`), even though it isn't directly used to prove `x + 0 = x`.

